                      <div align="left">
                      <table border="0" width="696" height="136">
                        <tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-06-20 - Gorden talks about PVP Teams (VZ/TZ) Status</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> Hello all,
<p>Due to the results of the /movelog command executed by players on the PvP-Teams
servers the weekend before last, we are reconsidering our decision to do the
move. Out of nearly 1800 accounts across TZ and VZ that requested move, only 278
asked to be moved from TZ (Coin only) to VZ (Coin and Item loot), while 1513
requested a move in the other direction.
<p>The result of completing this move would most likely result in crowding on
the Tallon Zek server while leaving Vallon Zek nearly empty. While we have
considered allowing a smaller number of people to move from Vallon to Tallon,
we have concluded that that would most likely be more destructive to server morale
than our current plan.
<p>As of now, and for the reasons stated above, our plan is to change the Vallon
Zek server to Coin-only loot making it identical to Tallon Zek in that respect.
<p>We will wait a few days to view comments here prior to finalizing the decision.
Please followup here with your thoughts.
<p>-Gordon<br>
</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='55' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> Source: EverQuest Announcments -  </font> <a href=http://http://www.everquest.com </a> http://www.everquest.com </td></tr>    
